10/07/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Justice Minister Vladam Batic said Wednesday (9 July) that a new court for prosecuting war criminals in Belgrade would begin functioning in September.
Deputy Chief Prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic is the main candidate for the post of local war crimes prosecutor.
In other news, Batic said he has asked UNMIK to hand over former Liberation Army of Presevo, Bujanovac and Medvedja(UCPBM) leader Shefqet Musliu to be prosecuted in Belgrade.
Earlier this week, Musliu was transferred from KFOR custody to UNMIK.
(BBC, B92, Beta, Tanjug, FoNet, Blic - 09/07/03)
